; Differential co-batch negate fixture (checkpoint (d), analysis sec 4.5 R9).
;
; ONE @differential message `sig(Tag, A, B)` feeds BOTH the pred relation
; (Tag 0 -> pr) AND the negated relation (Tag 1 -> blk), so a single epoch
; can carry changes to BOTH sides at once. This is the runtime-expressible
; co-batch (unlike the monotone two-message shape, where each message is its
; own epoch): both crossover arms live because blk is @differential, and one
; epoch can present r-add/r-remove x k-gain/k-loss in every combination.
;
; The four F-A mixed same-batch cases (analysis sec 2), r = pred row (pr),
; k = negated key (blk), required net counts:
;   (1) r added,   k gained: 0   (phantom pair: forward blocked, X- fires)
;   (2) r added,   k lost:   +1  (forward fires, X blocked)
;   (3) r removed, k gained: -1  (forward retract, X blocked)
;   (4) r removed, k lost:   0   (churn pair)
;
; out(A,B) is the observable: a pr(A,B) row published iff blk(A) absent.
#message sig(u64 Tag, u64 A, u64 B) @differential.

#local pr(u64 A, u64 B).
#local blk(u64 A).

#query out(free u64 A, free u64 B).

pr(A, B) : sig(0, A, B).
blk(A) : sig(1, A, _).

out(A, B) : pr(A, B), !blk(A).
